cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with foreground object segmentation in real environments. The use of generative adversarial network (GAN) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves image processing, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of back-propagation technique for generating background samples suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
